claim.claim-text:
1. A sonde, comprising:
a cylindrical hollow tube made of a ferromagnetic material and configured to removably receive a battery;
a coil surrounding the tube;
electronic drive circuit means connectable to the battery for supplying the coil with an electric signal that will induce the tube to emit electromagnetic signals at a predetermined strength and frequency that can be remotely detected;
a water-tight housing surrounding and enclosing the coil and the electronic drive circuit; and
means connectable to a rear end of the tube for sealing the same and configured for coupling to a snake or a drain cleaning machine.

5. A sonde, comprising:
a cylindrical hollow tube made of a ferromagnetic material and configured to removably receive a battery;
a coil surrounding the tube;
electronic drive circuit means abutting or longitudinally spaced from one end of the tube and connectable to the battery for supplying the coil with an electric signal that will induce the tube to emit electromagnetic signals at a predetermined strength and frequency that can be remotely detected;
a water-tight housing made of over-molded plastic surrounding and enclosing the coil and the electronic drive circuit;
means connectable to a rear end of the tube for sealing the same; and
the tube having a longitudinally extending slot to reduce eddy losses.

9. A sonde, comprising:
a cylindrical hollow tube made of a ferromagnetic material and configured to removably receive a battery;
a coil surrounding the tube;
electronic drive circuit means connectable to the battery for supplying the coil with an electric signal that will induce the tube to emit electromagnetic signals at a predetermined strength and frequency that can be remotely detected;
a water-tight housing surrounding and enclosing the coil and the electronic drive circuit;
means connectable to a rear end of the tube for sealing the same;
means for providing illumination mounted behind a transparent portion of the housing; and
means for energizing the illumination means using power from the battery to indicate a status of the electronic drive circuit means.

12. A sonde, comprising:
a cylindrical hollow tube made of a ferromagnetic material and configured to removably receive a battery;
a coil surrounding the tube;
electronic drive circuit means connectable to the battery for supplying the coil with an electric signal that will induce the tube to emit electromagnetic signals at a predetermined strength and frequency that can be remotely detected;
a water-tight housing surrounding and enclosing the coil and the electronic drive circuit;
means connectable to a rear end of the tube for sealing the same; and
water proof switch means for turning the electronic drive circuit means ON and OFF, the switch means being manually actuable by twisting the rear end sealing means.

17. A sonde, comprising:
a cylindrical hollow tube made of a ferromagnetic material and configured to removably receive a battery;
a coil surrounding the tube;
electronic drive circuit means connectable to the battery for supplying the coil with an electric signal that will induce the tube to emit electromagnetic signals at a predetermined strength and frequency that can be remotely detected;
a water-tight housing surrounding and enclosing the coil and the electronic drive circuit;
means connectable to a rear end of the tube for sealing the same;
a tubular protective outer case enclosing the water-tight housing and having a sealed rear end configured for coupling to a drain cleaning machine; and
a closure plug inserted into a forward end of the protective outer case.
